# OpenBeast configuration — copy to "openbeast.conf" and edit.
#
#   cp openbeast.conf.example openbeast.conf
#
# openbeast.conf is gitignored, so your local paths never get committed.

# Where your .gguf model weights live. Weights are large and are NOT stored in
# the repo — put them wherever you have space (NVMe, USB, NAS mount, etc.) and
# point OpenBeast at them here.
#
# Accepts absolute paths, ~ for your home dir, or a path relative to the repo.
# Resolution order (first match wins): the $OPENBEAST_WEIGHTS_DIR env var
# overrides everything (per-shell override), then WEIGHTS_DIR set here, then
# an existing ./weights/ inside the repo, then ../weights next to the repo.
#
# Examples:
#   WEIGHTS_DIR=/mnt/nvme/gguf
#   WEIGHTS_DIR=~/models/gguf
#   WEIGHTS_DIR=/run/media/max/USB-SSD/weights
#   WEIGHTS_DIR=/mnt/nas/ai/weights
#
# Leave commented to use the default resolution above (an existing ./weights
# inside the repo, else ../weights next to it — bootstrap.sh creates it).
#WEIGHTS_DIR=../weights

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Build  (see docs/HARDWARE_PROFILES.md)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# llama.cpp build backend, used by bootstrap.sh and scripts/update.sh --llama.
# "auto" (the default, even without this file) picks from the detected GPU
# vendor: NVIDIA→cuda, AMD→hip, Intel Arc→sycl, no GPU→cpu. Set it explicitly
# to override detection. Only cuda is measured by OpenBeast (reference: one
# RTX 5090); hip and sycl build but are untested. bootstrap.sh writes the
# resolved value here so updates always rebuild with the same backend.
# The $OPENBEAST_GPU_BACKEND env var overrides this per-shell.
#GPU_BACKEND=auto

# Daemon-mode memory cap, as a PERCENT of this machine's physical RAM
# (1-100; default 75). `./start.sh -d` computes the byte value fresh at
# every launch, so the cap adapts to the box automatically — a runaway
# process can OOM the stack's scope, never the system. Swap inside the
# scope is additionally capped at 8G regardless of this setting.
# The $OPENBEAST_MEM_LIMIT_PCT env var overrides this per-shell.
#MEM_LIMIT_PCT=75

# Serve script start.sh launches when none is given on the command line
# (also used by healthcheck.sh --restart when no supervisor is running).
# Must name an executable in scripts/. Env override: $OPENBEAST_SERVE_SCRIPT.
#SERVE_SCRIPT=serve-qwen-27b-uncensored-q5.sh

# Private workspace for files the CHAT model reads/writes via the direct
# tools (created 0700 by start.sh; spawned agents use their own workdir).
# Env override: $OPENBEAST_FILES_DIR.
#FILES_DIR=~/openbeast-files

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Network / remote access  (see docs/REMOTE_ACCESS_PLAN.md and
# scripts/setup-tailscale.sh — one command sets up secure access from
# anywhere via Tailscale)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Address the stack's services bind to. Default (even without this file) is
# 127.0.0.1: loopback-only, with remote devices coming in through Tailscale
# Serve's authenticated HTTPS proxy. Set 0.0.0.0 to restore the legacy
# LAN-open behavior (any device on your network can reach every service,
# unauthenticated — not recommended).
#BIND_HOST=127.0.0.1

# Optional: require "Authorization: Bearer <key>" on the llama-server API.
# Off by default — the tailnet is already the security boundary, and the
# eval harness / agents don't send a key yet. Enable if your tailnet has
# other users.
#LLAMA_API_KEY=

# Open WebUI login. Default OFF for local-only single-user installs (no
# login wall; configure-webui.sh auto-configures via the default admin
# account). scripts/setup-tailscale.sh sets this to true automatically when
# the WebUI goes tailnet-wide — that's when a per-user login + the RBAC
# tiers (docs/RBAC_PLAN.md) start to matter.
#WEBUI_AUTH=false

# Open WebUI admin credentials, used by scripts/configure-webui.sh to apply
# tool-server + native function-calling config when WEBUI_AUTH is on.
# Create the account in the browser on first visit, then mirror it here.
#WEBUI_ADMIN_EMAIL=
#WEBUI_ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Agent-spawn router  (see docs/RESEARCH_FINDINGS.md §8-11)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Opt-in proxy that reliably turns "spawn a background agent / do this in the
# background" chat requests into real agents. Local models won't call
# start_agent on their own judgment; the router detects the intent with a
# grammar-constrained pre-flight classification and spawns deterministically.
# When true, start.sh runs agents/router.py on ROUTER_PORT in front of
# llama-server (8080); WebUI/OpenCode point at it automatically. llama-server
# stays direct on 8080, so evals and spawned agents are never routed.
# Adds ~500ms to chat turns that look like delegation requests; normal turns
# pass through untouched (thinking stays ON). Default: false.
#AGENT_ROUTER=false
#ROUTER_PORT=8088
